@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<div class="markdown prose w-full break-words dark:prose-invert light">
    <p>
        Creating a comprehensive privacy policy for an employee management system is crucial for building trust and
        ensuring compliance with data protection laws. Here’s a sample privacy policy that you can customize for your
        organization:
    </p>
    <hr>
    <h2>Privacy Policy for Employee Management System</h2>
    <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> [Insert Date]</p>
    <h3>Introduction</h3>
    <p>
        At our company, we are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring the security of your personal
        information. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect the data we gather through our Employee
        Management System.
    </p>
    <h3>Information We Collect</h3>
    <p>We may collect the following types of personal information:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>
            <strong>Personal Identification Information</strong>: Name, address, email, phone number, date of birth, and
            other identifying details.
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Employment Information</strong>: Job title, department, employment history, performance evaluations, and
            training records.
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Attendance and Time Records</strong>: Clock-in/clock-out times, leave requests, and overtime
            information.
        </li>
        <li><strong>Payroll Information</strong>: Salary, bank account details, and tax-related information.</li>
    </ul>    
    <h3>Data Security</h3>
    <p>
        We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your personal information from
        unauthorized access, loss, misuse, or alteration. Access to personal data is restricted to authorized personnel
        only.
    </p>
    <h3>Data Retention</h3>
    <p>
        We will retain your personal information only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this
        policy or as required by law.
    </p>
    <h3>Your Rights</h3>
    <p>You have the following rights regarding your personal information:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Access</strong>: You can request access to the personal information we hold about you.</li>
        <li><strong>Correction</strong>: You can request corrections to any inaccurate or incomplete information.</li>
        <li>
            <strong>Deletion</strong>: You can request the deletion of your personal information under certain
            circumstances.
        </li>
        <li><strong>Objection</strong>: You can object to the processing of your personal data in certain situations.</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>Changes to This Privacy Policy</h3>
    <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated
        effective date. We encourage you to review this policy periodically for any updates.
    </p>
    <h3>Contact Us</h3>
    <p>If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us at:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Email</strong>: [Email Address]</li>
        <li><strong>Phone</strong>: [Phone Number]</li>
        <li><strong>Address</strong>: [Company Address]</li>
    </ul>
    <hr>
    <h3>Conclusion</h3>
    <p>
        Your privacy is important to us, and we are committed to safeguarding your personal information. Thank you for
        trusting [Your Company Name] with your data.
    </p>
    <hr>
    <p>Feel free to adjust the content to align with your organization’s specific practices and legal requirements!</p>
</div>
